This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with the task of question answering using Memory Networks. Additionally, the paper proposes extensions to the Dynamic Memory Network (DMN) which is a popular model in the field of natural language processing. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed model uses neural networks and attention mechanisms to improve performance on the task of question answering. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper deals with the training and evaluation of a machine learning model. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possibility as the proposed model uses neural networks and attention mechanisms. 

Finally, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with visual data, but the proposed model could potentially be applied to tasks involving visual question answering.
